b'All in all you could say, while Jorginho plays deeper, he is defensively not better than Pedri. While being also more secure but not as progressive. However Pedri can learn from his effectiveness when dribbling and pressing. Two important aspects for a midfielder.'

b'However when carrying higher on the pitch Pedri shows his superiority to the more deep Jorginho. The Italian Chelsea midfielder has 139 of them while Pedri blows him away with 204 of them. Seems Pedri loves a move up to the opponents box.'

b'Jorginho attempted only 34 dribbles but he completed 24 of them, giving him an amazing percentage of 70.6%. Highly effective! Pedri dribbles more with 64 times, but only 37 succesful ones leaves him with a percentage of 57.8%. Not bad though!'
b'Now the dribble and progression stats. Jorginho has the image of being very press resistant and being able to progress the ball easily and the stats back him up.'

b'Pedri has almost a similar amount of being succesful with 226 times but his attemption rate of 810 gives him a lower percentage of 27.9%. He does win the block battle yet again, with 75 against 68 for Jorginho. It seems to be Pedri\xe2\x80\x99s thing when defending.'

b'Jorginho, being a more deep midfielder for both club and country just slightly beats Pedri with succesful tackles: 62 against 55. The press stats do show how amazing Jorginho is. Jorginho applied pressure 685 times and was succesful 237 times, giving him a percentage of 34.6%. https://t.co/iZS6tAGoup'

b'The stats surprisingly show us Jorginho at 28 years old in his prime, does not necessarily seem to be a more progressive passer than 17-18 year old Pedri. A bit more secure, that yes but there is still a lot of time to improve. Let\xe2\x80\x99s look at defensive stats.'

b'However when it comes to key and progressive passing Pedri is arguably better! Jorginho gave only 32 keypasses compared to Pedri\xe2\x80\x99s 43. Progressive passing is slightly in Jorginho\xe2\x80\x99s favor with 169 against the 159 of Pedri but it is scarily close. https://t.co/ffwb4o0kQs'
